<ol><li>The <b>force on a small charge</b> is given by<b>&nbsp;</b>\(F=EQ\)</li><li>If the charge is moved from the positive to the negative plate, the work done on the charge&nbsp;\(W=Fd=QEd\)</li><li>By definition, the potential difference between the plates is the&nbsp;<b>work done per unit charge</b>&nbsp;when a small charge is moved through potential difference&nbsp;\(V\).\[\begin{align*}
V&amp;=\frac{W}{Q}\\
&amp;=\frac{QEd}{Q}\\
&amp;=Ed
\end{align*}\]Therefore&nbsp;\(E=\frac{V}{d}\)</li></ol>